From: Nicolas Ferre <nicolas.ferre@atmel.com>
Date: Tue, 6 Sep 2011 17:49:35 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 003/319] mmc: atmel-mci: support 8-bit buswidth

This patch adds support for 8-bit buswidth.
Relevant SDCR value modified.

Derived from a patch by Jaehoon Chung on dw_mmc.

Signed-off-by: Nicolas Ferre <nicolas.ferre@atmel.com>
---
 drivers/mmc/host/atmel-mci.c |    3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/mmc/host/atmel-mci.c b/drivers/mmc/host/atmel-mci.c
index 630b9bc..68917de 100644
--- a/drivers/mmc/host/atmel-mci.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/host/atmel-mci.c
@@ -1201,6 +1201,9 @@ static void atmci_set_ios(struct mmc_host *mmc, struct mmc_ios *ios)
 	case MMC_BUS_WIDTH_4:
 		slot->sdc_reg |= ATMCI_SDCBUS_4BIT;
 		break;
+	case MMC_BUS_WIDTH_8:
+		slot->sdc_reg |= ATMCI_SDCBUS_8BIT;
+		break;
 	}
 
 	if (ios->clock) {
